<TITLE> Islami Bank okays 25% stock dividend </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 18 (bdnews24.com)Islami Bank Bangladesh Friday approved a plan to announce a 25 percent stock dividend to shareholders for 2007. The board of directors made the decision at Thursday's meeting, the bank said in a statement. The board of directors also approved a bonus share against an existing four. The dividends will be announced at the bank's 25th annual general meeting, slated for Aug 29, according to a decision. The board meeting was chaired by the bank's chairman Abu Nasser Muhammad Abduz Zaher. Dr Abdulhameed Fouad Al-Khateeb, a sponsor of the bank, and Kuwait Awqaf Public Foundation's representative Ahmad Mohammed Thani also attended the meeting. The bank's authorised capital is Tk 5,000 million and paid-up capital is Tk 3,456 million recorded in 2006, up from Tk 67.50 million in 1983, when it started its activities, according to a Web posting. bd
